{"body": [{"indent": 0, "text": ["Stone Wall"], "type": "title", "extent": [69, 84], "level": 0}, {"indent": 0, "type": "summary", "extent": [84, 130], "text": ["Simulates an anti-aliased stone wall."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [130, 183], "text": ["This operator simulates an anti-aliased stone wall."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [183, 438], "text": ["The number of stones is roughly determined by the Cell Frequency (", {"text": ["cfreq"], "type": "code"}, ")\ninput. The shape of each piece of stone is controlled by the Shape\nFrequency (", {"text": ["sfreq"], "type": "code"}, ") and Shape Amplitude (", {"text": ["samp"], "type": "code"}, ") inputs. The higher either\nvalue, the more distorted the shape."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [438, 768], "text": ["The stone displacement consists of noisy bumps and cavities, whose\nrandomness is controlled by Bump Frequency (", {"text": ["bfreq"], "type": "code"}, "), Bump Amplitude\n(", {"text": ["bamp"], "type": "code"}, ") and Bump Roughness (", {"text": ["brough"], "type": "code"}, "). The amount of cavity chipping is\ndetermined by the Chip Amount (", {"text": ["chip"], "type": "code"}, ") input. By increasing the ", {"text": ["chip"], "type": "code"}, "\namount, you can make the stone look more porous."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [768, 1099], "text": ["The \"Pepper\" inputs refer to the additional color noise that is\n\"peppered\" over the stone surface to make it look more realistic. The\nlook of the pepper noise is controlled by three inputs: Pepper Amplitude\n(", {"text": ["pamp"], "type": "code"}, "), Pepper Roughness (", {"text": ["prough"], "type": "code"}, "), and Bump Frequency (", {"text": ["bfreq"], "type": "code"}, "). The\nPepper Color (", {"text": ["peppercolor"], "type": "code"}, ") specifies its color."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [1099, 1238], "text": ["Finally, the grooves between the stones come with size (", {"text": ["gwidth"], "type": "code"}, "),\nsoftness (", {"text": ["gsoft"], "type": "code"}, ") and grout (", {"text": ["groutcolor"], "type": "code"}, ", ", {"text": ["gfreq"], "type": "code"}, ", ", {"text": ["gamp"], "type": "code"}, ") controls."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [1238, 1873], "text": ["If the Position (", {"text": ["P"], "type": "code"}, "), Normal (", {"text": ["N"], "type": "code"}, ") and texture coordinate (", {"text": ["s"], "type": "code"}, " ", {"text": ["t"], "type": "code"}, ") inputs are\nnot connected, the global variables by the same names will be used\ninstead. Typically, you will use ", {"text": ["Rest Position"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/restpos", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/vop/restpos"}, " or ", {"text": ["UV Space Change"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/uvspacechg", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/vop/uvspacechg"}, " as\ninputs for ", {"text": ["P"], "type": "code"}, ", and Shading Layer Parameter as the input for ", {"text": ["s"], "type": "code"}, " and\n", {"text": ["t"], "type": "code"}, ". You will not touch ", {"text": ["N"], "type": "code"}, " unless you want to apply additional\ndisplacement to the stone wall using an operator such as ", {"text": ["Bump Map"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/bumpmap", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/vop/bumpmap"}, " or ", {"text": ["Furrows"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/furrows", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/vop/furrows"}, ". If you need to access the global variables directly, they are\navailable from the ", {"text": ["Global Variables"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/global", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/vop/global"}, " operator."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "extent": [1882, 1906], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/bricks", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/vop/bricks"}]}, {"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "extent": [1906, 1931], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/bumpmap", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/vop/bumpmap"}]}, {"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "extent": [1931, 1955], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/global", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/vop/global"}]}, {"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "extent": [1955, 1980], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/restpos", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/vop/restpos"}]}, {"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "extent": [1980, 2004], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/stone", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/vop/stone"}]}], "container": true, "type": "bullet_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 1, "text": "Related", "role": "section", "extent": [1873, 1882], "container": true, "type": "related_section", "id": "related"}], "summary": ["Simulates an anti-aliased stone wall."], "type": "root", "attrs": {"version": null, "namespace": null, "internal": "stonewall", "context": "vop", "type": "node", "icon": "VOP/stonewall"}, "title": ["Stone Wall"]}